---
id: org.dxos.plugin.crm
name: CrmPlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

A Composer plugin that contributes a **CRM blueprint** for researching people
and organizations and producing structured Profile documents in the user's
space. v1 is a library-layer plugin only — no UI surfaces. It is deliberately
thin: the heavy lifting (web research, database CRUD, markdown document
creation) is reused from existing `@dxos/assistant-toolkit` blueprints
(`research`, `database`, `markdown`). plugin-crm contributes CRM-specific
instructions, one relation schema, one image-attachment operation, and a
pluggable research-source contract for future extensions (e.g., a LinkedIn
browser-extension integration).

Given a reference to a `Person`, `Organization`, or an email `Message`, the
blueprint drives an agent to (a) locate or create the corresponding Person
and Organization ECHO objects, (b) produce a markdown Profile document
following an editable section template, (c) link the Profile to its subject
via a typed `ProfileOf` relation, and (d) attach a best-effort avatar /
company-logo image uploaded to the DXOS image service.

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.
Each extension is defined in the Appendix or resolved via its URI.

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`       |
| `feat`      | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`       |
| `test`      | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`       |
| `op`        | `org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0`         |
| `service`   | `org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0`    |
| `blueprint` | `org.dxos.mdl.blueprint@1.0`  |

## Types

```mdl
type ContactExtract
  desc: >
    Structured output of the email-signature extractor utility.
    Pure function; computed from a Message's sender + blocks.
  fields:
    fullName?: string
    email: string
    phone?: string
    orgName?: string               # e.g., "Silverline Partners"
    orgDomain?: string             # e.g., "silverline-partners.example" (from email host)
    locations?: string[]           # e.g., ["New York", "San Francisco"]
    urls?: string[]                # any URLs found in the signature block
    isFreeMailDomain: boolean      # gmail, outlook, icloud, yahoo, ...
```

```mdl
type ProfileOf
  desc: >
    ECHO relation linking a Profile Document to its subject (Person or Organization).
    A single Profile Document may have multiple ProfileOf relations when
    research covers both a Person and their Organization.
    Typename: org.dxos.relation.plugin-crm.profile-of
  fields:
    sources: string[]              # URLs / provider IDs that contributed to the profile
    lastResearchedAt: DateTime     # ISO 8601 UTC timestamp
    summary?: string               # 1–2 sentence abstract of the profile
  relation:
    source: Document               # org.dxos.type.document
    target: Person | Organization  # org.dxos.type.person | org.dxos.type.organization
```

```mdl
type ResearchSource
  desc: >
    Pluggable contract for augmenting the CRM blueprint with additional
    research tools. Consumers register a ResearchSource; the CRM blueprint
    picks up its tool definitions at build time. v1 defines the contract
    only — no implementations ship with the plugin. A planned future
    implementation ("LinkedIn via browser extension") will be provided by
    composer-crx.
  fields:
    id: string                     # stable identifier, e.g. "linkedin-crx"
    description: string            # human-readable; referenced in blueprint instructions
    tools: ToolDefinition[]        # tool defs contributed to the blueprint
  note: >
    The CRM blueprint's instructions explicitly mention the sources that
    are registered, so the agent knows to prefer them when appropriate.
```

## Blueprint

```mdl
blueprint CrmBlueprint
  key: org.dxos.blueprint.crm
  desc: >
    Drives an agent to research a contact (Person, Organization, or email
    Message) and produce a Profile document plus Person/Organization
    records in the user's space.
  depends_on:
    - org.dxos.blueprint.research    # Research, DocumentCreate operations (high-level synthesis)
    - org.dxos.blueprint.web-search  # Fetch operation + AnthropicWebSearch (low-level URL fetch + search)
    - org.dxos.blueprint.database    # object-create, object-update, query, relation-create, load
    - org.dxos.blueprint.markdown    # create/read/update markdown documents
  contributes:
    - plugin-crm/attach-image
    - plugin-crm/ProfileOf (schema registration)
    - tools from registered ResearchSource contracts (v1: none)
  instructions: >
    Authored in `src/blueprints/crm/instructions.ts`. Content is user-editable
    post-install via the blueprint editor. Covers:
      1. Subject resolution (branch on typename of the input ref).
      2. Email-based contact extraction from Message (sender + signature).
      3. Person/Organization lookup-or-create using the database blueprint.
      4. Free-mail domain heuristic: do not attach Organization from
         personal-email domains (gmail, outlook, icloud, yahoo, ...).
      5. Research invocation via the research blueprint.
      6. Profile composition following a section template (Overview,
         Background, Current Role, Organization, Key Links, Notes, Sources).
      7. ProfileOf relation creation linking the Document to its subject(s).
      8. Best-effort image attachment via the attach-image operation.
      9. Reply in the agent's normal reply style with inline object refs.
```

## Operations

```mdl
op attachImage
  desc: >
    Downloads an external image URL, re-uploads it to the DXOS image service
    (POST /thumbnail), and stores the returned canonical URL on the subject's
    `image` field. Mirrors the behaviour of composer-crx `createThumbnail`.
  input:
    subject: Ref<Person | Organization>
    url: string                    # external image URL
  output:
    imageUrl: string               # canonical URL returned by the image service
  errors:
    ConfigMissing: imageServiceUrl is not configured
    FetchFailed: unable to download the source image
    UnsupportedContentType: source content-type is not an accepted image format
    UploadFailed: image service rejected the upload
  effects: [http, echo:write]
  requires: [Database, Config, Trace]
  note: >
    Accepted content types: image/jpeg, image/png, image/webp, image/gif.
    SVG is rejected because inline <script> and event handlers make it a
    stored-XSS risk when downstream surfaces embed the image via <object>
    or <iframe>. Content type is inferred from the response or URL
    extension. Failures are returned as structured errors so the agent can
    continue without the image.
```

## Services

```mdl
service ImageService
  desc: >
    DXOS EDGE image service. Accepts a multipart/form-data upload with a
    single `file` field and returns a JSON body containing a canonical
    `url`. Used by composer-crx today and reused verbatim by attach-image.
  loading: lazy
  ops:
    postThumbnail(blob: Blob) → { url: string }
  errors:
    RateLimited: too many requests
    InvalidUpload: the posted file is not an accepted image
  note: >
    Endpoint is `${config.imageServiceUrl}/thumbnail`. The field name `file`
    is shared with composer-crx and should eventually be factored into a
    protocol def.
```

```mdl
service AssistantToolkit
  desc: >
    Reused blueprints and operations from @dxos/assistant-toolkit.
  loading: eager
  ops:
    research.Research(query, instructions?, entityExtraction?)
    research.DocumentCreate(subject, name, content) → { document: DXN }
    webSearch.Fetch(url) → content              # low-level URL fetch
    webSearch.AnthropicWebSearch                # native Anthropic web search tool
    database.objectCreate(typename, fields) → Obj
    database.objectUpdate(ref, fields) → Obj
    database.query(filter) → Obj[]
    database.relationCreate(typename, source, target, fields) → Relation
    database.load(ref) → Obj
    markdown.*                     # create/read/update — Document-level utilities
  note: >
    plugin-crm never reimplements these. The CRM blueprint declares its
    dependency on the corresponding blueprints so they are loaded alongside.
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Polymorphic Subject Resolution
  desc: >
    The blueprint accepts a Ref<Person | Organization | Message> and
    branches deterministically based on the loaded object's typename.
  req F-1.1: Blueprint instructions describe how to load the subject via database.load.
  req F-1.2: Instructions describe the three branches (Person, Organization, Message).
  req F-1.3:
    when: subject is a Message
    then: agent extracts { fullName, email, phone?, orgName?, orgDomain?, locations? }
          from sender + signature blocks
  req F-1.4:
    when: subject is a Person
    then: agent seeds research from Person.fullName, Person.emails, and Person.organization (if set)
  req F-1.5:
    when: subject is an Organization
    then: agent seeds research from Organization.name and Organization.website
```

```mdl
feat F-2: Contact Extractor Utility
  desc: >
    Pure function used by tests and available as reference output for the
    agent. Stable deterministic behaviour makes signature parsing
    regression-testable independently of the LLM loop.
  req F-2.1: extractContactFromMessage(msg: Message) → ContactExtract is a pure, synchronous function.
  req F-2.2: Extractor reads Message.sender.name, Message.sender.email, Message.properties.subject, and all text blocks.
  req F-2.3: Domain part of the sender email determines orgDomain, excluding free-mail domains.
  req F-2.4: Phone numbers are detected via a permissive regex (international + US formats).
  req F-2.5: URLs in the signature block are captured into urls[].
  req F-2.6: Multi-city office strings (e.g., "Americas (New York, San Francisco, ...)") parse into locations[].
  req F-2.7: Free-mail detection covers at minimum: gmail.com, outlook.com, icloud.com, yahoo.com, hotmail.com, protonmail.com.
```

```mdl
feat F-3: Person & Organization Upsert
  desc: >
    The blueprint's instructions guide the agent to deduplicate by email
    and by organization domain/name before creating new objects.
  req F-3.1:
    when: an email address is known
    then: agent queries existing Person objects for emails containing that address
  req F-3.2:
    when: no matching Person exists
    then: agent creates a new Person with extracted fields via database.objectCreate
  req F-3.3:
    when: a matching Person exists
    then: agent updates it via database.objectUpdate with newly discovered fields (non-destructive)
  req F-3.4:
    when: orgDomain or orgName is known
    then: agent queries existing Organization objects by website or name
  req F-3.5:
    when: no matching Organization exists AND domain is not free-mail
    then: agent creates a new Organization
  req F-3.6:
    when: a Person has an Organization
    then: agent ensures Person.organization references the Organization
```

```mdl
feat F-4: Research & Profile Composition
  desc: >
    The blueprint delegates web research to the research blueprint and
    composes a Profile markdown document following an editable section
    template defined in the blueprint instructions.
  req F-4.1: Blueprint instructions define a default section template: Overview, Background, Current Role, Organization, Key Links, Notes, Sources.
  req F-4.2: Sections are editable via the blueprint editor (instructions are part of the blueprint object).
  req F-4.3: Agent invokes research.Research with a composed query derived from { fullName, orgName, orgDomain }.
  req F-4.4: Agent creates a Document via research.DocumentCreate with the subject ref and the composed markdown content.
  req F-4.5: The "Notes" section records disambiguation hints and uncertainty (e.g., free-mail sender, ambiguous name).
  req F-4.6: The "Sources" section lists URLs that contributed to the profile.
```

```mdl
feat F-5: ProfileOf Relation
  desc: >
    A typed relation links the Profile Document to its subject. This is
    the primary mechanism for discovering profiles from a Person or
    Organization.
  req F-5.1: ProfileOf schema is registered into the space's schema registry at plugin init.
  req F-5.2:
    when: a Profile Document is created for a Person
    then: a ProfileOf relation is created with source=Document, target=Person
  req F-5.3:
    when: a Profile Document also covers an Organization
    then: an additional ProfileOf relation is created with target=Organization
  req F-5.4: Relation carries sources[], lastResearchedAt, and summary.
```

```mdl
feat F-6: Image Attachment
  desc: >
    Best-effort avatar / logo retrieval. The agent finds candidate URLs via
    the existing fetch_url / web search tools; plugin-crm uploads them to
    the DXOS image service and writes the canonical URL onto the ECHO
    object.
  req F-6.1: attachImage operation uploads via POST /thumbnail and writes the result URL to subject.image.
  req F-6.2: imageServiceUrl is read from @dxos/config at invocation time.
  req F-6.3:
    when: imageServiceUrl is not configured
    then: operation returns ConfigMissing error; agent continues without image
  req F-6.4:
    when: image upload fails
    then: operation returns a structured error; subject.image is not modified
  req F-6.5: No fallback search path inside attachImage — the agent is responsible for supplying the URL.
```

```mdl
feat F-7: Pluggable Research Sources
  desc: >
    Future sources (notably LinkedIn via browser extension) will register
    additional tools into the CRM blueprint. v1 defines the contract but
    ships no implementations.
  req F-7.1: ResearchSource TypeScript interface is exported from src/sources.
  req F-7.2: The CRM blueprint picks up registered sources' tools at blueprint.make() time.
  req F-7.3: Blueprint instructions enumerate the currently-registered sources by id + description so the agent knows what is available.
  req F-7.4: No ResearchSource is bundled in v1; composer-crx will ship the first one in a later PR.
```

```mdl
feat F-8: Configuration Surface (deferred)
  desc: >
    Per-space CrmSettings ECHO type is planned but not implemented in v1.
    v1 relies on @dxos/config for imageServiceUrl and uses only no-auth
    public endpoints for search (inherited from the research blueprint).
  req F-8.1: v1 does NOT ship a CrmSettings schema.
  req F-8.2: Design allows adding CrmSettings later without breaking API — the attachImage operation reads from Config for now.
  req F-8.3: No API keys are required to run v1.
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: Extractor — corporate short signature
  given: an email Message with sender "Priya Adebayo <padebayo@ventura-advisors.example>" and signature block
         containing "Priya Adebayo / padebayo@ventura-advisors.example / (555) 010-0149"
  when: extractContactFromMessage(msg) is called
  then:
    - fullName === "Priya Adebayo"
    - email === "padebayo@ventura-advisors.example"
    - phone === "(555) 010-0149"
    - orgDomain === "ventura-advisors.example"
    - isFreeMailDomain === false
```

```mdl
test T-2: Extractor — free-mail personal contact
  given: an email Message with sender "Riley Nakamura <riley.nakamura@gmail.com>" and no corporate signature
  when: extractContactFromMessage(msg) is called
  then:
    - fullName === "Riley Nakamura"
    - email === "riley.nakamura@gmail.com"
    - orgDomain === "gmail.com"
    - isFreeMailDomain === true
    - orgName is undefined
```

```mdl
test T-3: Extractor — corporate rich multi-office signature
  given: an email Message with sender "Saskia Volkov <Saskia.Volkov@silverline-partners.example>" and signature
         block "Saskia Volkov / +1 555 010 4182 / www.silverline-partners.example /
         Americas (New York, Buenos Aires, Chicago, Miami, San Francisco, São Paulo, Washington DC)"
  when: extractContactFromMessage(msg) is called
  then:
    - fullName === "Saskia Volkov"
    - email === "Saskia.Volkov@silverline-partners.example"
    - phone === "+1 555 010 4182"
    - orgDomain === "silverline-partners.example"
    - urls contains "www.silverline-partners.example"
    - locations contains "New York"
    - locations contains "San Francisco"
    - isFreeMailDomain === false
```

```mdl
test T-4: Full-loop playground — corporate short signature (tuning)
  given: a space with the corporate-short email inserted as a Message, memoized LLM, stubbed attachImage, stubbed search
  when: the CRM blueprint is invoked with the Message ref
  then:
    - a Person exists whose emails contains "padebayo@ventura-advisors.example"
    - an Organization exists whose website ends with "ventura-advisors.example" OR whose name contains "Ventura Advisors"
    - Person.organization references the Organization
    - a Document exists whose content contains "## Overview" and "## Sources"
    - a ProfileOf relation exists with source=Document, target=Person
    - a ProfileOf relation exists with source=Document, target=Organization
```

```mdl
test T-5: Full-loop playground — free-mail personal contact
  given: a space with the freemail-personal email inserted as a Message, memoized LLM, stubbed attachImage, stubbed search
  when: the CRM blueprint is invoked with the Message ref
  then:
    - a Person exists whose emails contains "riley.nakamura@gmail.com"
    - NO Organization has been created solely because of the sender domain
    - the Profile Document's Notes section mentions any former affiliations surfaced in the message body
    - a ProfileOf relation exists with source=Document, target=Person
```

```mdl
test T-6: Full-loop playground — corporate rich signature
  given: a space with the corporate-rich-signature email inserted as a Message, memoized LLM, stubbed attachImage, stubbed search
  when: the CRM blueprint is invoked with the Message ref
  then:
    - a Person exists whose emails contains "Saskia.Volkov@silverline-partners.example"
    - an Organization exists whose website ends with "silverline-partners.example" OR whose name contains "Silverline Partners"
    - Organization.location or the Profile Document mentions at least one office city
    - a Document exists following the section template
    - ProfileOf relations exist for both Person and Organization
```

```mdl
test T-7: attachImage — success path
  given: imageServiceUrl is configured; the mock image service returns { url: "https://images.dxos.org/abc" };
         a Person exists with no image
  when: attachImage({ subject: personRef, url: "https://example.com/avatar.png" }) is called
  then:
    - the mock image service received a multipart POST with field "file"
    - Person.image === "https://images.dxos.org/abc"
    - operation output.imageUrl === "https://images.dxos.org/abc"
```

```mdl
test T-8: attachImage — config missing
  given: imageServiceUrl is not configured in @dxos/config
  when: attachImage({ subject: personRef, url: "https://example.com/avatar.png" }) is called
  then:
    - operation returns a structured error tagged ConfigMissing
    - Person.image is unchanged
    - the agent can continue without aborting the run
```

```mdl
test T-9: Graduation — assistant-e2e suite
  given: stable memoized fixtures in packages/core/assistant-e2e/src/testing/crm/fixtures/
  when: CI runs the assistant-e2e test suite
  then:
    - the 3 email fixtures produce the same Person / Organization / Document / ProfileOf graph as the playground tests
    - assertions are tight (exact field values, not substring matches)
  tags: [deferred, post-tuning]
```

---

## Design Notes

### Composition over duplication

The single most important architectural decision is that plugin-crm is a thin
composition layer. The `research`, `web-search`, `database`, and `markdown`
blueprints in `@dxos/assistant-toolkit` already provide, respectively,
high-level synthesis (`Research` / `DocumentCreate`), low-level URL fetch +
native Anthropic web search (`Fetch` / `AnthropicWebSearch`), CRUD on ECHO
objects, and Document lifecycle. plugin-crm declares a dependency on these
blueprints; the agent sees their tools alongside `attach-image` and drives
the CRM workflow per the instructions. This means:

- No new `upsert_person` / `upsert_organization` / `create_profile_document` / `search_web` / `fetch_url` tools.
- The agent is responsible for orchestration — matching Q5 (agent-orchestrated) and Q11 (compose).
- Tuning the CRM behaviour is primarily a prompt-engineering exercise on the blueprint instructions.

### LinkedIn / browser extension seam

LinkedIn is out of scope for v1 code. The `ResearchSource` TypeScript interface
is defined in `src/sources/research-source.ts`, and the blueprint's `make()`
function iterates over any registered sources and includes their tools in the
blueprint's tool list. No sources are registered by default. The planned
future implementation will live in `composer-crx` and communicate with the
user's authenticated LinkedIn session via the browser.

### Image attachment — no fallback search

`attach-image` does not itself search for candidate images. The agent finds
them (favicon, OG image, public Gravatar, company-website logo) via the
web-search blueprint's `Fetch` operation and `AnthropicWebSearch` tool, then
passes the URL to `attach-image`. This keeps the operation small,
single-purpose, and mockable in tests.

### Free-mail domains

A conservative allowlist of free-mail domains (gmail, outlook, icloud, yahoo,
hotmail, protonmail) is treated as "no organization signal from email alone".
This prevents the free-mail fixture (riley.nakamura@gmail.com) from creating a
"Gmail" or "Google" organization purely from the sender domain. The blueprint
instructions call this out so the agent does not override the heuristic from
body-text hints unless the user explicitly asks.

### Profile section template

The default section template lives in the blueprint instructions (prose), not
in a separate schema or a template Document. This makes the template
user-editable through the existing blueprint editor surface without
introducing new ECHO types. Sections: **Overview**, **Background**, **Current
Role**, **Organization**, **Key Links**, **Notes**, **Sources**.

### Testing strategy

Three layers:

1. **Extractor unit tests** (`src/util/extract-contact.test.ts`) — pure, fast, CI-on-by-default, one test per email.
2. **Tuning playground** (`src/blueprints/crm/blueprint.test.ts`) — memoized LLM + stubbed image/search; `.skip` by default; regenerable with `ALLOW_LLM_GENERATION=1`. Used to iterate on instructions against the 3 emails.
3. **Graduated assistant-e2e suite** (`packages/core/assistant-e2e/src/testing/crm/`) — tight assertions, canonical CI; populated once playground behaviour is stable.

### Out of scope for v1

- UI surfaces (no react-surface, no article/object view, no settings panel).
- `CrmSettings` ECHO type (planned; see F-8).
- Any ResearchSource implementation, including LinkedIn.
- API-keyed search providers (Tavily, Brave, Google CSE, Clearbit, etc.).
- Deduping of multiple Person matches by fuzzy-name — v1 updates the best match or asks the user.
- Image-quality heuristics — v1 accepts whatever candidate URL the agent supplies.

---

## Appendix: Extension Definitions

Extension block types used in this document. Types not redefined here (`type`,
`feat`, `test`, `op`, `service`) follow the definitions in the shared DXOS
MDL extension library (see `packages/plugins/plugin-discord/PLUGIN.mdl`
appendix for reference).

```mdl
ext blueprint
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.blueprint@1.0
  desc: >
    A named blueprint declaration describing its key, dependencies on other
    blueprints, its contributed operations/schemas, and a prose summary of
    its instructions. The blueprint's actual instruction text lives in
    source (src/blueprints/<name>/instructions.ts) and is out of scope for
    this document's extension schema.
  fields:
    key: string                  # blueprint identifier (e.g. org.dxos.blueprint.crm)
    desc?: Prose
    depends_on?: string[]        # other blueprint keys this blueprint composes with
    contributes?: string[]       # operations / schemas introduced by this blueprint
    instructions?: Prose         # summary; authoritative text lives in code
```
